definition.value: This is an AE which is a rare condition in which a brain develops without the cerebellum.
This is an AE which is  papillary neoplasms of neuroectodermal origin arising from the choroid plexus epithelium of the cerebral ventricles.

This is an AE which can be categorized into those with a lack of origin or ostial atresia, an abnormal origin such as an anomalous origin off the pulmonary artery or off an abnormal aortic sinus, or an anomalous course (such as a single coronary coursing between the pulmonary artery and aorta) or a coronary artery fistula.
This is an AE which is a congenital closed sac, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue .
This is an AE which comprise a spectrum of anomalies that include pulmonary sequestrations, congenital lobar emphysema, bronchogenic cysts, and congenital cystic adenomatoid malformations.
This is an AE which refers to a condition where cytomegalovirus is transmitted in the prenatal period.
This is an AE which is rare and is a tumor that originates in the connective fibrous tissue found at the ends of long bones and then spreads to other surrounding soft tissues.
This is an AE which is a physical anomaly that is deleterious, i.e. foot defect  perceived as a problem.
This is an AE which is an autosomal-recessive disorder characterized by generalized lack of adipose tissue either at birth or within the first year of life.
This is an AE which is frequent, usually isolated anomalies, but may exist as part of a syndrome.
This is an AE which is an infectious disease caused by the hepatitis B virus (HBV) that affects the liver;it is a type of  congenital viral hepatitis.
This is an AE which is rare, with congenital HSV infection by intrauterine infection accounting for <5% of cases of HSV infection in the perinatal period.
This is an AE which is a type of hernia in which abdominal organs (typically the stomach) slip through the diaphragm into the middle compartment of the chest.
This is an AE which is a condition in which an accumulation of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) occurs within the brain.
This is an AE which defined as congenital dilatation of one or more components of the renal collecting system, is detected in 1-2% of all pregnancies.
This is an AE which is thyroid hormone deficiency present at birth.
This is an AE which is an abnormality of the structure of  jaw.

This is an AE which is a widely used term for a congenital malformation, i.e. a congenital, physical anomaly such as joint and is recognizable at birth, and which is significant enough to be considered a problem.
This is an AE which is an indication for complete evaluation to establish the cause of the airway obstruction.
This is an AE which is a birth defect in which nerves are missing from parts of the intestine.
This is an AE which is a relatively rare and highly complex cardiac disease.
This is an AE which is a complex, etiologically diverse, clinical descriptor identified in a variety of diagnoses characterized by multiple congenital joint contractures.
This is an AE which is an abnormality of the structure of a body musculoskeletal part.
This is an AE which is a type of melanocytic nevus (or mole) found in infants at birth.
This is an AE which may be overt or subtle and can occasionally cause life-threatening emergencies at birth.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory condition of the lung primarily at birth affecting the small air sacs known as alveoli .
This is an AE which represent a diverse group of abnormalities, ranging from asymptomatic incidental findings to causes of sudden cardiac death.
This is an AE which is a condition of increased blood pressure within the arteries of the lungs at birth.

This is an AE which is often the result of congenital malformations and is observed in isolation or as part of a larger pathologic process, as in Tetralogy of Fallot, Noonan syndrome, and congenital rubella syndrome.

This is an AE which is often the result of congenital malformations and is observed in isolation or as part of a larger pathologic process, as in Tetralogy of Fallot, Noonan syndrome, and congenital rubella syndrome.
This is an AE which is a condition present at birth regardless of its cause which occured on renal.
This is an AE which  can occur in a developing fetus of a pregnant woman who has contracted rubella, usually in the first trimester.
This is an AE which is syphilis present in utero and at birth, and occurs when a child is born to a mother with syphilis.
This is an AE which is a neoplasm containing tissues foreign to the site of origin or containing more than one embryonic germ cell layer.
This is an AE which can occurs spontaneous and excessive bleeding.
This is an AE which is a genetically and clinically heterogeneous group of platelet disorders that are characterized by thrombocytopenia since birth.
This is an AE which is a rare occurrence and associates with cleft palate may be considered as evidence of close interrelation of embryogenesis of the tongue and palate.
This is an AE which is defined as a contracture or fibrosis of the Sternocleidomastoid muscle, on one side, leading to a homolateral inclination and contralateral rotation of the face and chin.

This is an AE which is a type of congenital valvular heart disease in which the tricuspid valve of the heart, located between the right atrium and right ventricle, does not close completely when the right ventricle contracts (systole).
This is an AE which is a health condition where the abdominal wall behind the navel is congenital damaged.
This is an AE which might be associated with a detrimental effect on the probability of pregnancy achievement, spontaneous abortion and on the obstetric outcome of each pregnancy.
This is an AE which is a congenital condition in which urine flows retrograde, or backward, from the bladder into one or both ureters and then to the renal calyx or kidneys.
This is an AE which is a defect in the structure of the heart or great vessels that is present at birth.

This is an AE which is small dilated blood vessels that can occur near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter and is  congenital.
.
This is an AE which is often associated with abnormal PA hemodynamics including increased pressure drop (p) and reduced asymmetric flow (Q), which may result in right ventricular dysfunction.
This is an AE which is a congenital heart valve disorder. Blood going from the heart to the lungs goes through the pulmonary valve, whose purpose is to prevent blood from flowing back to the heart.
This is an AE which is the arrangement of digits (fingers and toes) on the hands, feet, or sometimes wings of a tetrapod animal.

This is an AE which is a congenital oral anomaly that may decrease the mobility of the tongue tip and is caused by an unusually short, thick lingual frenulum, a membrane connecting the underside of the tongue to the floor of the mouth.
This is an AE which is a rare disorder characterized by congenital absence of skin.
This is an AE which  refers to a lens opacity which is present at birth.
